    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brentano</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-23T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1924—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 24—12:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Your December 22, 3 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d171fn1">See footnote 92, <ref
                            target="#pg_232">p. 232</ref>.</note> and January 18, 7 p.m.” Foreign
                    Office writes that the Government authorizes the aviators to fly over and land
                    in Hungary and that it will inform me later regarding landing points and
                    restrictions against photography.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Brentano</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
